<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>rpxy – Advanced Usage</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/</link><description>Recent content in Advanced Usage on rpxy</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>HTTP/3</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/http3/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/http3/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; can serve HTTP/3 requests thanks to &lt;a href="https://github.com/quinn-rs/quinn"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;quinn&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://github.com/aws/s2n-quic"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;s2n-quic&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://github.com/hyperium/h3"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;hyperium/h3&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. To enable this experimental feature, add an entry &lt;code&gt;experimental.h3&lt;/code&gt; in your &lt;code&gt;config.toml&lt;/code&gt; like follows. Then, any TLS-enabled application can be served with HTTP/3 in addition to HTTP/2 and HTTP/1.1 &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/client_auth/"&gt;except for the applications with TLS client authentication&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;experimental&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;h3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alt_svc_max_age&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;3600&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;request_max_body_size&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;65536&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_concurrent_connections&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;10000&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_concurrent_bidistream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_concurrent_unistream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_idle_timeout&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;Any values in the entry like &lt;code&gt;alt_svc_max_age&lt;/code&gt; are optional.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>TLS Client Authentication</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/client_auth/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/client_auth/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;TLS client authentication is enabled when &lt;code&gt;apps.&amp;quot;app_name&amp;quot;.tls.client_ca_cert_path&lt;/code&gt; is set for the domain specified by &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;app_name&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;apps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;localhost&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;server_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;localhost&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# Domain name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;tls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;https_redirection&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;tls_cert_path&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;./server.crt&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;tls_cert_key_path&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;./server.key&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;client_ca_cert_path&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;./client_cert.ca.crt&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;Currently we have a limitation on HTTP/3 support for applications that enables client authentication. If an application is set with client authentication, HTTP/3 doesn&amp;rsquo;t work for the application.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>ACME (Let's Encrypt) Integration</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/acme/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/acme/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;In addition to &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/basics/2_tls/"&gt;use static files of certificates and private keys&lt;/a&gt;, the automatic issuance and renewal of certificates, i.e., ACME (Automated Certificate Management Environment) standardized as &lt;a href="https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8555"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;RFC8555&lt;/a&gt;, are available in &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt;. To enable this feature, you need to specify the following entries for each application requiring ACME in the configuration file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml:config.toml" data-lang="toml:config.toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# TLS port, which is also used for ACME challenge.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;listen_port_tls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;443&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# ACME enabled domain name.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Note that acme option must be specified in the experimental section.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;apps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;app_with_acme&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;server_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;example.org&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;reverse_proxy&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;location&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;app1.local:8080&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;tls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;https_redirection&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;acme&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# do not specify tls_cert_path and/or tls_cert_key_path&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACME will be used to get a certificate for the &lt;code&gt;server_name&lt;/code&gt; with ACME &lt;a href="https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8737"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;TLS-ALPN-01&lt;/code&gt; (RFC8737)&lt;/a&gt; protocol. So all you need is to open
the TLS port 443 to the public. Also in this case, you don&amp;rsquo;t need to specify &lt;code&gt;tls_cert_path&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;tls_cert_key_path&lt;/code&gt; for the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For every ACME enabled domain, the following settings are referred to acquire a certificate and a private key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml:config.toml" data-lang="toml:config.toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Global ACME settings. Unless specified, ACME is disabled.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;experimental&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;acme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Email address for ACME registration.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;email&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;test@example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Optional: ACME directory URL. [default: &amp;#34;https://acme-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory&amp;#34;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;dir_url&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;https://acme-staging-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Optional: Directory storing retrieved certificates and private keys, which is relative to the current working directory. [default: &amp;#34;./acme_registry&amp;#34;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;registry_path&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;./acme_registry&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The above configuration is common to all ACME enabled domains. Note that the https port must be open to the public to prove the domain ownership.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Caching</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/cache/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/cache/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; takes an approach to cache responses in a &lt;em&gt;hybrid&lt;/em&gt; way of temporary files and on-memory objects.
If &lt;code&gt;[experimental.cache]&lt;/code&gt; is specified in &lt;code&gt;config.toml&lt;/code&gt;, you can leverage the local caching feature using temporary files and on-memory objects. An example configuration is as follows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# If this specified, file cache feature is enabled&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;experimental&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;cache&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;cache_dir&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;./cache&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# optional. default is &amp;#34;./cache&amp;#34; relative to the current working directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_cache_entry&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# optional. default is 1k&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_cache_each_size&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;65535&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# optional. default is 64k&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;max_cache_each_size_on_memory&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;4096&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# optional. default is 4k if 0, it is always file cache.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;em&gt;storable&lt;/em&gt; (in the context of an HTTP message) response is stored if its size is less than or equal to &lt;code&gt;max_cache_each_size&lt;/code&gt; in bytes. If it is also less than or equal to &lt;code&gt;max_cache_each_size_on_memory&lt;/code&gt;, it is stored as an on-memory object. Otherwise, it is stored as a temporary file. Note that &lt;code&gt;max_cache_each_size&lt;/code&gt; must be larger or equal to &lt;code&gt;max_cache_each_size_on_memory&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;Once &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; restarts or the config is updated, the cache is totally eliminated not only from the on-memory table but also from the file system.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Post-Quantum Cryptography</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/post_quantum/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/post_quantum/</guid><description>
&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="overview"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#overview" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; provides cutting-edge security by supporting post-quantum cryptography, protecting your applications against future quantum computing threats. This feature is enabled by default and requires no special configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is Post-Quantum Cryptography?&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="what-is-post-quantum-cryptography"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#what-is-post-quantum-cryptography" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post-quantum cryptography refers to cryptographic algorithms that are secure against attacks by quantum computers. As quantum computing technology advances, traditional cryptographic methods like RSA and ECC may become vulnerable. Post-quantum algorithms are designed to remain secure even when powerful quantum computers become available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;rpxy&amp;rsquo;s Implementation&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="rpxys-implementation"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#rpxys-implementation" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Technical Foundation&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="technical-foundation"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#technical-foundation" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; enables post-quantum cryptography through the &lt;a href="https://github.com/rustls/rustls/tree/main/rustls-post-quantum"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;rustls-post-quantum&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; library, which provides post-quantum key exchange algorithms for rustls. This integration allows &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; to offer cutting-edge cryptographic security with minimal configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Hybrid Key Exchange&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="hybrid-key-exchange"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#hybrid-key-exchange" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; implements &lt;strong&gt;hybrid post-quantum key exchange&lt;/strong&gt; that combines:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classical cryptography&lt;/strong&gt; (X25519) - Proven security for current threats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post-quantum cryptography&lt;/strong&gt; (ML-KEM 768) - Protection against quantum attacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This hybrid approach provides:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backward compatibility&lt;/strong&gt; with existing systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Future-proof security&lt;/strong&gt; against quantum threats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance optimization&lt;/strong&gt; without sacrificing security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Supported Algorithms&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="supported-algorithms"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#supported-algorithms" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;X25519MLKEM768&lt;/strong&gt;: This is the hybrid key exchange algorithm supported by &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt;, combining X25519 elliptic curve cryptography with ML-KEM 768 (formerly Kyber768) post-quantum cryptography.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Protocol Coverage&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="protocol-coverage"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#protocol-coverage" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post-quantum cryptography is supported across all secure protocols:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TLS 1.3&lt;/strong&gt; - All HTTPS connections use post-quantum key exchange&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUIC and HTTP/3&lt;/strong&gt; - Post-quantum security for next-generation protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automatic negotiation&lt;/strong&gt; - Clients and servers negotiate the best available algorithm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Configuration&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="configuration"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#configuration" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Default Behavior&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="default-behavior"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#default-behavior" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post-quantum cryptography is &lt;strong&gt;enabled by default&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt;. No configuration changes are required:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Post-quantum TLS is automatically enabled for all applications&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;apps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;secure_app&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;server_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;reverse_proxy&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;location&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;backend:8080&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;tls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;https_redirection&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Verification&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="verification"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#verification" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can verify post-quantum key exchange is active by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Checking TLS handshake logs&lt;/strong&gt; - Look for &lt;code&gt;MLKEM768&lt;/code&gt; or something like that in debug output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using OpenSSL s_client&lt;/strong&gt; - Examine cipher suite negotiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network analysis tools&lt;/strong&gt; - Inspect TLS handshake packets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Security Benefits&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="security-benefits"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#security-benefits" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Current Protection&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="current-protection"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#current-protection" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traditional threats&lt;/strong&gt; - RSA, ECC still secure against classical computers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Side-channel attacks&lt;/strong&gt; - Rust&amp;rsquo;s memory safety provides additional protection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perfect forward secrecy&lt;/strong&gt; - Session keys remain secure even if long-term keys are compromised&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Future Protection&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="future-protection"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#future-protection" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quantum resistance&lt;/strong&gt; - Algorithms designed to withstand quantum attacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Long-term security&lt;/strong&gt; - Data encrypted today remains secure in the quantum era&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cryptographic agility&lt;/strong&gt; - Easy transition to new algorithms as standards evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Performance Impact&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="performance-impact"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#performance-impact" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimal Overhead&lt;/strong&gt;: The hybrid approach ensures post-quantum security while maintaining excellent performance. Key exchange operations are optimized and cached where possible.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Industry Standards&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="industry-standards"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#industry-standards" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt;&amp;rsquo;s post-quantum implementation follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IETF drafts&lt;/strong&gt; - Implements &lt;a href="https://www.ietf.org/archive/id/draft-kwiatkowski-tls-ecdhe-mlkem-03.html"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;draft-kwiatkowski-tls-ecdhe-mlkem-03&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-tls-hybrid-design/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;draft-ietf-tls-hybrid-design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NIST standards&lt;/strong&gt; - Uses standardized ML-KEM (FIPS 203) cryptographic primitives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry adoption&lt;/strong&gt; - Compatible with other implementations following the same IETF drafts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard Status&lt;/strong&gt;: The X25519MLKEM768 algorithm is based on IETF draft specifications (&lt;a href="https://www.ietf.org/archive/id/draft-kwiatkowski-tls-ecdhe-mlkem-03.html"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;draft-kwiatkowski-tls-ecdhe-mlkem-03&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-tls-hybrid-design/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;draft-ietf-tls-hybrid-design&lt;/a&gt;) while using the standardized ML-KEM (FIPS 203) post-quantum cryptographic primitives.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Compatibility&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="compatibility"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#compatibility" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Client Support&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="client-support"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#client-support" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Modern browsers and HTTP clients increasingly support post-quantum key exchange:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chrome/Chromium&lt;/strong&gt; - Experimental support available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Firefox&lt;/strong&gt; - Support in development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OpenSSL&lt;/strong&gt; - Recent versions support hybrid algorithms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Fallback Behavior&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="fallback-behavior"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#fallback-behavior" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;If clients don&amp;rsquo;t support post-quantum algorithms, &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; automatically falls back to classical cryptography, ensuring compatibility while providing enhanced security when possible.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>